('Sony PlayStation 2 Slim - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Sony', '<p>Sony PlayStation 2 Slim board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (8)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_CPU</strong> - CPU - Main processor</li><li><strong>U_GPU</strong> - GPU - Graphics processor</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - System RAM</li><li><strong>J_ODD</strong> - Connector - Optical drive ribbon connector</li><li><strong>U_BIOS</strong> - BIOS ROM - BIOS / boot ROM</li><li><strong>J_CTRL</strong> - Connector - Controller ports</li><li><strong>U_AV</strong> - A/V Encoder - Video encoder / DAC</li><li><strong>J_PSU</strong> - Connector - Power supply connector</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>5V (5V): 5.0 V @ on - Regulated 5V logic supply.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (later boards).</li></ul>', 'Sony PlayStation 2 Slim board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_CPU CPU  Main processor U_GPU GPU  Graphics processor U_RAM RAM  System RAM J_ODD Connector  Optical drive ribbon connector U_BIOS BIOS ROM  BIOS / boot ROM J_CTRL Connector  Controller ports U_AV A/V Encoder  Video encoder / DAC J_PSU Connector  Power supply connector 5V 5V 5.0 V on 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on'),
('Sony PlayStation 3 - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Sony', '<p>Sony PlayStation 3 board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (9)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_APU</strong> - APU / CPU - Main APU or CPU+GPU</li><li><strong>U_SB</strong> - Southbridge - I/O southbridge</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - GDDR / system memory</li><li><strong>U_HDMI</strong> - HDMI IC - HDMI encoder / retimer</li><li><strong>U_NAND</strong> - NAND Flash - Onboard flash</li><li><strong>U_PMIC</strong> - PMIC - Power management IC</li><li><strong>J_ODD</strong> - Connector - Optical drive connector</li><li><strong>J_HDMI</strong> - Connector - HDMI port</li><li><strong>J_FAN</strong> - Connector - Cooling fan connector</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>STBY_5V (STBY_5V): 5.0 V @ standby - Standby supply present when plugged in.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ standby - Housekeeping 3.3V.</li><li>12V (12V): 12.0 V @ on - Main 12V rail from PSU (where applicable).</li></ul>', 'Sony PlayStation 3 board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_APU APU / CPU  Main APU or CPU+GPU U_SB Southbridge  I/O southbridge U_RAM RAM  GDDR / system memory U_HDMI HDMI IC  HDMI encoder / retimer U_NAND NAND Flash  Onboard flash U_PMIC PMIC  Power management IC J_ODD Connector  Optical drive connector J_HDMI Connector  HDMI port J_FAN Connector  Cooling fan connector STBY_5V STBY_5V 5.0 V standby 3V3 3V3 3.3 V standby 12V 12V 12.0 V on'),
