('Nintendo NES - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo NES board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (8)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_CPU</strong> - CPU / Processor - Main processor</li><li><strong>U_PPU</strong> - Video / PPU - Picture processing unit</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - Work/video RAM</li><li><strong>J_CART</strong> - Connector - Cartridge edge connector</li><li><strong>J_CTRL</strong> - Connector - Controller port(s)</li><li><strong>U_REG</strong> - Voltage Regulator - 5V regulator (e.g. 7805)</li><li><strong>J_PWR</strong> - Connector - Power input connector</li><li><strong>J_AV</strong> - Connector - A/V or RF output</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>5V (5V): 5.0 V @ on - Regulated 5V logic supply.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (later boards).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo NES board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_CPU CPU / Processor  Main processor U_PPU Video / PPU  Picture processing unit U_RAM RAM  Work/video RAM J_CART Connector  Cartridge edge connector J_CTRL Connector  Controller port(s) U_REG Voltage Regulator  5V regulator (e.g. 7805) J_PWR Connector  Power input connector J_AV Connector  A/V or RF output 5V 5V 5.0 V on 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on'),
('Nintendo Super Nintendo (SNES) - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Super Nintendo (SNES) board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (8)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_CPU</strong> - CPU / Processor - Main processor</li><li><strong>U_PPU</strong> - Video / PPU - Picture processing unit</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - Work/video RAM</li><li><strong>J_CART</strong> - Connector - Cartridge edge connector</li><li><strong>J_CTRL</strong> - Connector - Controller port(s)</li><li><strong>U_REG</strong> - Voltage Regulator - 5V regulator (e.g. 7805)</li><li><strong>J_PWR</strong> - Connector - Power input connector</li><li><strong>J_AV</strong> - Connector - A/V or RF output</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>5V (5V): 5.0 V @ on - Regulated 5V logic supply.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (later boards).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Super Nintendo (SNES) board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_CPU CPU / Processor  Main processor U_PPU Video / PPU  Picture processing unit U_RAM RAM  Work/video RAM J_CART Connector  Cartridge edge connector J_CTRL Connector  Controller port(s) U_REG Voltage Regulator  5V regulator (e.g. 7805) J_PWR Connector  Power input connector J_AV Connector  A/V or RF output 5V 5V 5.0 V on 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on'),
('Nintendo Nintendo 64 - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Nintendo 64 board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (8)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_CPU</strong> - CPU / Processor - Main processor</li><li><strong>U_PPU</strong> - Video / PPU - Picture processing unit</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - Work/video RAM</li><li><strong>J_CART</strong> - Connector - Cartridge edge connector</li><li><strong>J_CTRL</strong> - Connector - Controller port(s)</li><li><strong>U_REG</strong> - Voltage Regulator - 5V regulator (e.g. 7805)</li><li><strong>J_PWR</strong> - Connector - Power input connector</li><li><strong>J_AV</strong> - Connector - A/V or RF output</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>5V (5V): 5.0 V @ on - Regulated 5V logic supply.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (later boards).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Nintendo 64 board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_CPU CPU / Processor  Main processor U_PPU Video / PPU  Picture processing unit U_RAM RAM  Work/video RAM J_CART Connector  Cartridge edge connector J_CTRL Connector  Controller port(s) U_REG Voltage Regulator  5V regulator (e.g. 7805) J_PWR Connector  Power input connector J_AV Connector  A/V or RF output 5V 5V 5.0 V on 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on'),
('Nintendo GameCube - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo GameCube board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (8)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_CPU</strong> - CPU - Main processor</li><li><strong>U_GPU</strong> - GPU - Graphics processor</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - System RAM</li><li><strong>J_ODD</strong> - Connector - Optical drive ribbon connector</li><li><strong>U_BIOS</strong> - BIOS ROM - BIOS / boot ROM</li><li><strong>J_CTRL</strong> - Connector - Controller ports</li><li><strong>U_AV</strong> - A/V Encoder - Video encoder / DAC</li><li><strong>J_PSU</strong> - Connector - Power supply connector</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>5V (5V): 5.0 V @ on - Regulated 5V logic supply.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (later boards).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo GameCube board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_CPU CPU  Main processor U_GPU GPU  Graphics processor U_RAM RAM  System RAM J_ODD Connector  Optical drive ribbon connector U_BIOS BIOS ROM  BIOS / boot ROM J_CTRL Connector  Controller ports U_AV A/V Encoder  Video encoder / DAC J_PSU Connector  Power supply connector 5V 5V 5.0 V on 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on'),
('Nintendo Wii - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Wii board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (8)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_CPU</strong> - CPU - Main processor</li><li><strong>U_GPU</strong> - GPU - Graphics processor</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - System RAM</li><li><strong>J_ODD</strong> - Connector - Optical drive ribbon connector</li><li><strong>U_BIOS</strong> - BIOS ROM - BIOS / boot ROM</li><li><strong>J_CTRL</strong> - Connector - Controller ports</li><li><strong>U_AV</strong> - A/V Encoder - Video encoder / DAC</li><li><strong>J_PSU</strong> - Connector - Power supply connector</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>5V (5V): 5.0 V @ on - Regulated 5V logic supply.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (later boards).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Wii board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_CPU CPU  Main processor U_GPU GPU  Graphics processor U_RAM RAM  System RAM J_ODD Connector  Optical drive ribbon connector U_BIOS BIOS ROM  BIOS / boot ROM J_CTRL Connector  Controller ports U_AV A/V Encoder  Video encoder / DAC J_PSU Connector  Power supply connector 5V 5V 5.0 V on 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on'),
('Nintendo Wii U - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Wii U board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (9)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_APU</strong> - APU / CPU - Main APU or CPU+GPU</li><li><strong>U_SB</strong> - Southbridge - I/O southbridge</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - GDDR / system memory</li><li><strong>U_HDMI</strong> - HDMI IC - HDMI encoder / retimer</li><li><strong>U_NAND</strong> - NAND Flash - Onboard flash</li><li><strong>U_PMIC</strong> - PMIC - Power management IC</li><li><strong>J_ODD</strong> - Connector - Optical drive connector</li><li><strong>J_HDMI</strong> - Connector - HDMI port</li><li><strong>J_FAN</strong> - Connector - Cooling fan connector</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>STBY_5V (STBY_5V): 5.0 V @ standby - Standby supply present when plugged in.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ standby - Housekeeping 3.3V.</li><li>12V (12V): 12.0 V @ on - Main 12V rail from PSU (where applicable).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Wii U board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_APU APU / CPU  Main APU or CPU+GPU U_SB Southbridge  I/O southbridge U_RAM RAM  GDDR / system memory U_HDMI HDMI IC  HDMI encoder / retimer U_NAND NAND Flash  Onboard flash U_PMIC PMIC  Power management IC J_ODD Connector  Optical drive connector J_HDMI Connector  HDMI port J_FAN Connector  Cooling fan connector STBY_5V STBY_5V 5.0 V standby 3V3 3V3 3.3 V standby 12V 12V 12.0 V on'),
('Nintendo Switch - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Switch board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (10)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_SOC</strong> - SoC - Main system-on-chip</li><li><strong>J_LCD</strong> - Connector - LCD / display connector</li><li><strong>J_BATT</strong> - Connector - Battery connector</li><li><strong>U_CHG</strong> - Charging IC - Battery charging IC</li><li><strong>J_BTN</strong> - Connector - Button / control flex</li><li><strong>U_PMIC</strong> - PMIC - Power management IC</li><li><strong>J_CART</strong> - Connector - Game card / cartridge connector</li><li><strong>U1</strong> - Charging IC - <code>M92T36</code> - USB-C PD / charging IC</li><li><strong>U3</strong> - Display Mux - <code>P13USB</code> - USB / display mux</li><li><strong>U6</strong> - Battery Charger - <code>BQ24193</code> - Battery charger IC</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>VBAT (VBAT): 3.7 V @ off - Battery rail (3.0-4.2V).</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (typical).</li><li>1V8 (1V8): 1.8 V @ on - 1.8V rail (typical).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Switch board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_SOC SoC  Main system-on-chip J_LCD Connector  LCD / display connector J_BATT Connector  Battery connector U_CHG Charging IC  Battery charging IC J_BTN Connector  Button / control flex U_PMIC PMIC  Power management IC J_CART Connector  Game card / cartridge connector U1 Charging IC M92T36 USB-C PD / charging IC U3 Display Mux P13USB USB / display mux U6 Battery Charger BQ24193 Battery charger IC VBAT VBAT 3.7 V off 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on 1V8 1V8 1.8 V on'),
('Nintendo Switch Lite - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Switch Lite board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (10)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_SOC</strong> - SoC - Main system-on-chip</li><li><strong>J_LCD</strong> - Connector - LCD / display connector</li><li><strong>J_BATT</strong> - Connector - Battery connector</li><li><strong>U_CHG</strong> - Charging IC - Battery charging IC</li><li><strong>J_BTN</strong> - Connector - Button / control flex</li><li><strong>U_PMIC</strong> - PMIC - Power management IC</li><li><strong>J_CART</strong> - Connector - Game card / cartridge connector</li><li><strong>U1</strong> - Charging IC - <code>M92T36</code> - USB-C PD / charging IC</li><li><strong>U3</strong> - Display Mux - <code>P13USB</code> - USB / display mux</li><li><strong>U6</strong> - Battery Charger - <code>BQ24193</code> - Battery charger IC</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>VBAT (VBAT): 3.7 V @ off - Battery rail (3.0-4.2V).</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (typical).</li><li>1V8 (1V8): 1.8 V @ on - 1.8V rail (typical).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Switch Lite board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_SOC SoC  Main system-on-chip J_LCD Connector  LCD / display connector J_BATT Connector  Battery connector U_CHG Charging IC  Battery charging IC J_BTN Connector  Button / control flex U_PMIC PMIC  Power management IC J_CART Connector  Game card / cartridge connector U1 Charging IC M92T36 USB-C PD / charging IC U3 Display Mux P13USB USB / display mux U6 Battery Charger BQ24193 Battery charger IC VBAT VBAT 3.7 V off 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on 1V8 1V8 1.8 V on'),
