('Nintendo Game Boy Micro - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Game Boy Micro board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (7)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_SOC</strong> - SoC - Main system-on-chip</li><li><strong>J_LCD</strong> - Connector - LCD / display connector</li><li><strong>J_BATT</strong> - Connector - Battery connector</li><li><strong>U_CHG</strong> - Charging IC - Battery charging IC</li><li><strong>J_BTN</strong> - Connector - Button / control flex</li><li><strong>U_PMIC</strong> - PMIC - Power management IC</li><li><strong>J_CART</strong> - Connector - Game card / cartridge connector</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>VBAT (VBAT): 3.7 V @ off - Battery rail (3.0-4.2V).</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (typical).</li><li>1V8 (1V8): 1.8 V @ on - 1.8V rail (typical).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Game Boy Micro board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_SOC SoC  Main system-on-chip J_LCD Connector  LCD / display connector J_BATT Connector  Battery connector U_CHG Charging IC  Battery charging IC J_BTN Connector  Button / control flex U_PMIC PMIC  Power management IC J_CART Connector  Game card / cartridge connector VBAT VBAT 3.7 V off 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on 1V8 1V8 1.8 V on'),
('Nintendo Nintendo DS - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Nintendo DS board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (7)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_SOC</strong> - SoC - Main system-on-chip</li><li><strong>J_LCD</strong> - Connector - LCD / display connector</li><li><strong>J_BATT</strong> - Connector - Battery connector</li><li><strong>U_CHG</strong> - Charging IC - Battery charging IC</li><li><strong>J_BTN</strong> - Connector - Button / control flex</li><li><strong>U_PMIC</strong> - PMIC - Power management IC</li><li><strong>J_CART</strong> - Connector - Game card / cartridge connector</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>VBAT (VBAT): 3.7 V @ off - Battery rail (3.0-4.2V).</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (typical).</li><li>1V8 (1V8): 1.8 V @ on - 1.8V rail (typical).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Nintendo DS board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_SOC SoC  Main system-on-chip J_LCD Connector  LCD / display connector J_BATT Connector  Battery connector U_CHG Charging IC  Battery charging IC J_BTN Connector  Button / control flex U_PMIC PMIC  Power management IC J_CART Connector  Game card / cartridge connector VBAT VBAT 3.7 V off 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on 1V8 1V8 1.8 V on'),
