('Nintendo Virtual Boy - Component Reference', 'Device Components/Nintendo', '<p>Nintendo Virtual Boy board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision.</p><h2>Components (8)</h2><ul><li><strong>U_CPU</strong> - CPU / Processor - Main processor</li><li><strong>U_PPU</strong> - Video / PPU - Picture processing unit</li><li><strong>U_RAM</strong> - RAM - Work/video RAM</li><li><strong>J_CART</strong> - Connector - Cartridge edge connector</li><li><strong>J_CTRL</strong> - Connector - Controller port(s)</li><li><strong>U_REG</strong> - Voltage Regulator - 5V regulator (e.g. 7805)</li><li><strong>J_PWR</strong> - Connector - Power input connector</li><li><strong>J_AV</strong> - Connector - A/V or RF output</li></ul><h2>Test points &amp; known-good rails</h2><ul><li>5V (5V): 5.0 V @ on - Regulated 5V logic supply.</li><li>3V3 (3V3): 3.3 V @ on - 3.3V rail (later boards).</li></ul>', 'Nintendo Virtual Boy board. Component set and rails are era-typical reference values; confirm exact values against the boardview/schematic for this revision. U_CPU CPU / Processor  Main processor U_PPU Video / PPU  Picture processing unit U_RAM RAM  Work/video RAM J_CART Connector  Cartridge edge connector J_CTRL Connector  Controller port(s) U_REG Voltage Regulator  5V regulator (e.g. 7805) J_PWR Connector  Power input connector J_AV Connector  A/V or RF output 5V 5V 5.0 V on 3V3 3V3 3.3 V on'),
